  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_6' aria-label=\" Rajendra Singh and Ors. versus State of Uttaranchal Etc. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('6','2025','2025_10_342_353','2025INSC1193'); ><font size='4'> <strong>RAJENDRA SINGH AND ORS.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF UTTARANCHAL ETC. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 10 S.C.R. 342</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1193</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004552025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PANKAJ MITHAL<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, PRASANNA BHALACHANDRA VARALE</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose as regards the correctness of the order passed by the High Court convicting the appellants u/s.302 IPC; and whether the appellants are the real persons who chased the deceased and killed him. Headnotes&dagger; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; s.302 &ndash; Murder Altercation between the parties over a land dispute &ndash; Few hours later, the appellants armed with swords and sharp edged weapon inflicted blows upon the son of the complainant resulting in his death &ndash; Acquittal by the trial court, however, conviction of the appellants-father, son<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 07-10-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 476/2013</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('6','2025','2025_10_342_353','2025INSC1193','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</